課程概述 Course Description
       The concept of research is gaining more and more attention nowadays. Research provides important evidence to guide clinical practice (evidence-based practice) and to direct the development of knowledge. This course introduces basic components of research, including quantitative and qualitative research models, literature search, research designs and methodology. In addition, this course will go over concepts regarding abilities needed to have for being a consumer of research, such as locating the literature, evaluating evidence, and synthesizing research. Moreover, in view of the trend of e-learning, this course will incorporate “i-teach” course platform and students are encouraged to download course materials, hand in assignments, exchange ideas through this platform. Upon finishing the course, students will be able to read and understand journal articles and to evaluate the research reports.The concept of research is gaining more and more attention nowadays. Research provides important evidence to guide clinical practice (evidence-based practice) and to direct the development of knowledge. This course introduces basic components of research, including quantitative and qualitative research models, literature search, research designs and methodology. In addition, this course will go over concepts regarding abilities needed to have for being a consumer of research, such as locating the literature, evaluating evidence, and synthesizing research. Moreover, in view of the trend of e-learning, this course will incorporate “i-teach” course platform and students are encouraged to download course materials, hand in assignments, exchange ideas through this platform. Upon finishing the course, students will be able to read and understand journal articles and to evaluate the research reports.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    1.    Students will demonstrate knowledge of basic elements of quantitative research design (e.g., constructs, variable, and hypotheses).
2.    Student will demonstrate knowledge of the logic of hypotheses testing and the relationship of statistical procedures and test statistics to this process.
3.    Students will be able to discuss and apply principles of validity in the design and critique of research. 
4.    Students will be able to identify, critique, and apply principles of reliability and validity of measurement.


